{"session_id": 64, "bill_id": 22906, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1105, "bill_title": "allow for a good cause exception to the time for an involuntary commitment hearing.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Courts and Judiciary", "Executive/Judiciary Request"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2022-01-24T10:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/hju09.mp3", "start_seconds": 461.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-01-24T10:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/hju09.mp3", "start_seconds": 461.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-01-24T10:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/hju09.mp3", "start_seconds": 461.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-01-24T10:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/hju09.mp3", "start_seconds": 461.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-02-01T08:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/sju14.mp3", "start_seconds": 4008.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-02-01T08:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/sju14.mp3", "start_seconds": 4008.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-02-01T08:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/sju14.mp3", "start_seconds": 4008.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2022-02-01T08:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2022/sju14.mp3", "start_seconds": 4008.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 22906, "bill_version_id": 228636, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2022-01-21T12:31:00.523-06:00", "bill_text": "An Act to allow for a good cause exception to the time for an involuntary commitment hearing. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That \u00a7 27A-10-8 be AMENDED: 27A-10-8. Within five days after the person is taken into custody, within six days if there is a Saturday, Sunday, or holiday within that time period, or within seven days if there is a Saturday, Sunday, and holiday within that time period, the person shall must be provided an involuntary commitment hearing. The hearing may be continued for good cause prior to the running of the applicable time period. The referring county shall pay any expenses incurred by the board holding the hearing, including the transportation of the person to the hearing, subject to reimbursement by the county ultimately proven to be the county of residence. No lien may be placed against the person for the expenses incurred by the board holding the hearing, including the transportation of the person to the hearing."}, {"bill_id": 22906, "bill_version_id": 232280, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2022-02-03T10:21:42.773-06:00", "bill_text": "ENTITLED An Act to allow for a good cause exception to the time for an involuntary commitment hearing. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That \u00a7 27A-10-8 be AMENDED: 27A-10-8. Within five days after the person is taken into custody, within six days if there is a Saturday, Sunday, or holiday within that time period, or within seven days if there is a Saturday, Sunday, and holiday within that time period, the person must be provided an involuntary commitment hearing. The hearing may be continued for good cause prior to the running of the applicable time period. The referring county shall pay any expenses incurred by the board holding the hearing, including the transportation of the person to the hearing, subject to reimbursement by the county ultimately proven to be the county of residence. No lien may be placed against the person for the expenses incurred by the board holding the hearing, including the transportation of the person to the hearing. An Act to allow for a good cause exception to the time for an involuntary commitment hearing. I certify that the attached Act originated in the: House as Bill No. 1105 Chief Clerk Speake